This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the development and evaluation of a Statistical Machine Translation system for medical texts. The paper also explores the effects of various training methods on the translation system, which involves the use of language models and phrase tables, and the evaluation of translation results using various metrics. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of various machine learning techniques such as factored phrase models and hierarchical models. 

Additionally, the paper may fall under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of an AI system for translation. 

The sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possibility as the paper involves the use of alignment methods for data preparation. 

Finally, the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society) may be relevant as the paper deals with the translation of medical texts, which has implications for healthcare and society as a whole.
